<br>
Everyone in the group worked equally hard for loot.. why should some (insert class here) get (insert that classes loot here) .. just for being that class?  I normally let whoever needs a item get it, but not all people do.  <br>
<br>
If a CSS will help someone get a better item on the trade market, by all means they should be able to do that.  Not everyone is in a high lvl guild and can get good stuff in raids.  <br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, Greed is just plane rood.  But let everyone have a equal shot at the loot.  I group in velks all the time (as most of you know) I am almost always at ledge (or soloing)..   any ledge group I'm in has 1 loot rule!!<br>
<br>
all roll, 1 loot per. (gems are for classes who can use)<br>
<br>
that clears up all the confusion.. and if you win the (insert crappy rare loot here) and (insert better loot here) drops .. you get to roll .. if you win you turn in the old loot which is re-rolled on by the rest of the group.<br>
<br>
